Remoting Sensing Helping Disaster Work in Tibet
LHASA , December 24 ( Xinhua ) -- The meteorology department of Tibet has used remoting sensing technology to monitor disasters and the environment to help avoid heavy losses .
According to a meteorology department official , technicians can monitor forest fires and predict the scale of fires .
Tibet , which is on the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau , has constant problems with natural disasters , but the department has been successful in forecasting large snow disasters and heavy floods , and the remote sensing information and weather forecasts have become important in policy decisions .
The remote sensing technology can be used for monitoring the growth of forage grass as well and the region has established a research center for further application of the technology .
